## When to use this component

Use this component when you need to present content, such as guidance or search results, across multiple pages.

You might do this when:
- showing all the content on a single page makes the page take too long to load
- the user may benefit from bookmarking or linking to specific pages of the content
- most users will only need the content on the first few pages

## When not to use this component

Only break up content into pages if it makes your service faster or easier to use.

Avoid using the 'infinite scroll' technique to automatically load content when the user approaches the bottom of the page. This causes problems for keyboard users.

## How it works

Add the pagination component after the content on each page that you have broken up.

