### For pages in a list

For pages where the user might need to jump back and forth, add numbered page links, as well as the previous and next links, like this:

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "default", html: true, nunjucks: true, titleSuffix: "second" }) }}

Show the page number in the page title so the user can see it in browser tabs and bookmarks. For example 'Search results (page 1 of 4)'.

Do not show pagination if there's only one page of content.

Redirect the user to the first page if they enter a URL of a page that no longer exists.

#### Previous and next links

Previous and next links are labelled 'Previous page' and 'Next page'. You can
visually hide the word 'page' to save horizontal space.

