### For large numbers of pages

Depending on the screen size, show an appropriate number of pages to fit the horizontal space available.

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "ellipses", html: true, nunjucks: true }) }}

For smaller screens, show page numbers for:
- the current page
- previous and next pages
- first and last pages

For larger screens, show page numbers for:
- the current page
- at least one page immediately before and after the current page 
- first and last pages

Use ellipses (…) to replace any skipped pages.

For example:
- **[1]** 2 … 100
- 1 **[2]** 3 … 100
- 1 2 **[3]** 4 … 100
- 1 2 3 **[4]** 5 … 100
- 1 … 4 **[5]** 6 … 100
- 1 … 97 **[98]** 99 100
- 1 … 98 **[99]** 100
- 1 … 99 **[100]**

### Filtering and sorting lists

If the user filters or sorts the list, apply their choice to the whole list, and not just the current page. Also redirect them back to the first page of the new results.

Set the number of items per page and the sorting algorithm so that most users find what they need on the first page.

